President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump hosted King Felipe VI and Queen Letizia of Spain at the White House on June 19, 2018. The visit marked the culmination of the royal family's tour of the United States, which aimed to celebrate the historic and cultural ties between the two countries that span over 300 years. During the meeting, the President and the King reaffirmed a 30-year bilateral military alliance and their commitment to NATO. They also discussed ways to strengthen economic and security ties, balance transatlantic trade, and diversify Europe's sources of energy. President Trump expressed his support for a strong and united Spain that takes a leading role in Europe.